<h3 id="ssb-protocol-improvement-proposal-spip" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#ssb-protocol-improvement-proposal-spip" aria-hidden="true">#</a> SSB Protocol Improvement Proposal (SPIP)</h3>
<ul>
<li><RouterLink to="/specs/spip-01.html">spip-01 : invite-code flow</RouterLink></li>
<li><RouterLink to="/specs/spip-02.html">spip-02 : message flow</RouterLink></li>
<li><RouterLink to="/specs/spip-03.html">spip-03 : decentralized identifier</RouterLink></li>
</ul>
<p>The SPIP process begins with a proposal from an individual or a group within the community. The proposal is then reviewed and discussed by other members, such as developers and users.</p>
<p>Simultaneously or subsequently, it can be implemented and coded. Then the proposal can be thoroughly examined. After a vote, the code is merged.</p>
<p>One of the main advantages of the SPIP process is that it provides a structured and transparent approach to improving the SSB protocol. By allowing proposals to be reviewed and discussed by the community, SPIPs help ensure that protocol changes are well-approved and receive broad support.</p>
